<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT,
        TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the four camshaft bushings for wear and proper running clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure camshaft bushing journal diameter using a micrometer. Measure at two locations
                    and record the readings.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using a telescoping gauge and micrometer, measure the camshaft bushing I.D. with bushing
                    installed in the crankcase). Record the readings.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Subtract the readings obtained in steps a and b, to determine running clearance.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded (see
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150501.xml" xrefid="hl4150501">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>), replace the
                    camshaft bushings using the camshaft bushing remover and installer
                    <emph type="bold">SE-2893</emph>.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150524" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11269" filename="../figcg1/CG11269.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.24 Installing Camshaft Drive Gear.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
